PsionEdge wrote:So is the shadow dude gone now? You can only fuck summon him for one mission?Spoilered background stuff from the books:
Spoiler: show
In ACoK, Renly is encamped at Bitterbridge - not too far from Tyrell seat of Highgarden - and is having his tournament when Catelyn Stark finds him. Shortly afterwards, he receives word that Stannis has laid siege to Storm's End, which is Renly's own seat. Renly leaves behind all his infantry and takes his van - all mounted and roughly 20,000 strong, IIRC - and races to meet Stannis at Storm's End, taking Catelyn with him as well. After "negotiations" with Stannis fail, he prepares for battle, but in the early morning, as Brienne is helping him don his armor, and Catelyn is trying to talk him out of fighting his brother, a shadow appears in the tent and slits his throat, slicing right through a heavy steel gorget. Catelyn and Brienne flee, Renly's knights go over to Stannis, while Loras Tyrell goes back to Bitterbridge to take control of the large army Renly left behind. Ser Cortnay Penrose, the castellan of Storm's End, continues to defy Stannis, which is when he has Davos row Melisandre into a cavern under the castle to birth another shadow, which kills Ser Cortnay, and the young knight who replaces him surrenders the castle to Stannis.The shadows are indeed single-use, and summoning them is implied to take away some of Stannis's life force - after two, Melisandre mentions that making a third one will kill him.
