dferrantino wrote:andyfatbastard wrote:Just watched the latest ep. The best scene by far was Maisie Williams and Charles Dance acting the shit out of each other. I thought Renly going was way too early in the ep, made it feel anticlimactic.Disagreed re Renly. Considering how they left off the episode before that, opening with Renly's death was the only way to go, and it's the catalyst for nearly everything else that happens in the south during this episode.I read a good article about one of the troubles with a story like this, as opposed to more "normal" network show is that there is little room for adjustment. While they are staying somewhat close to the books there are obviously some changes but nothing too drastic. This does not all for the flexibility for a good character to stay around.Without reading the book I thought the Renly did die a little quick. I was curious about his relationship with Anne Bolyn. In a more traditional show the producers may have decided he was an interesting character to keep around.Take Walter Grogin's Boyd Crowder from Justified. MINOR SPOILER FOR THE JUSTIFIED PILOT Spoiler: show
In the original pilot of the show he was killed at the end. Obviously he was so great the producers decided to keep him around and make him the co-star of the show.
That kind of flexibility is one of the drawbacks of having the main story already written.Not really making a judgment either way, just thought it was interesting.
